[SN]TITLE[SN]
The Qualifiers: Leigh Centurions 32-26 Salford Red Devils

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Leigh Centurions maintained their perfect start to the Qualifiers with victory over Salford Red Devils.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
First-half tries from Reni Maitua, Cory Patterson and Gregg McNally gave Leigh a 10-point lead at the break.
Mason Caton-Brown scored twice for Salford, with Niall Evalds, Robert Lui and Ben Murdoch-Masila also crossing as they got within four points.
However, further Centurion scores from Adam Higson and Matty Dawson extended their winning streak to 15 games.
